The paper deals with the Delaunay triangulations and complexes, which are fundamental concepts in computational geometry (cs.CG). The Dushnik-Miller dimension is a combinatorial invariant that measures the complexity of partially ordered sets, and it is used in the paper to study the topology of the TD-Delaunay complexes (cs.DM). The paper also involves graph theory (cs.GT) and algebraic topology (cs.MG, cs.SD) to prove the main result and disprove the conjecture.
